function.name: agent_registry_invoke_agent
function.arguments: {"agentId":"summarizer_agent","agentInput":"{\"data\":\"War and Peace is a historical novel by Leo Tolstoy, first published in 1869. The story is set against the backdrop of the Napoleonic Wars and follows the lives of several aristocratic families in Russia, particularly focusing on the characters of Pierre Bezukhov, Prince Andrei Bolkonsky, and Natasha Rostova. The novel explores themes of fate, free will, and the nature of history, as it intertwines personal stories with the larger events of war and society. Through the characters' experiences, Tolstoy examines the impact of war on individuals and the moral dilemmas they face. The narrative shifts between the personal struggles of the characters and the broader historical context, ultimately portraying the complexity of life and the interconnectedness of human experiences.\"}"}
